# Personal — {{OWNER_NAME}}

_The non-work context the agency needs to be useful. Family,
health, friends, commitments that aren't work but shape the work.
Read by CoS for triage; read by anyone scheduling or interrupting._

_This is sensitive. Only agents that genuinely need this context
load it. Audit checks `personal-md-read` access._

_Derived from interview {{INTERVIEW_DATE}}._

---

## Family

{{FAMILY_CONTEXT}}

_(Spouse / partner, children, parents, siblings as relevant. Names,
ages where relevant, any standing commitments tied to family time.
Hard-blocked time and the rules around it.)_

## Health + energy

{{HEALTH_CONTEXT}}

_(Sleep schedule, exercise commitments, energy patterns through the
day, any medical considerations the agency needs to honor when
scheduling.)_

## Friends + community

{{FRIENDS_COMMUNITY}}

_(Standing relationships outside work. Friend groups, community
involvement, religious/spiritual practice, civic obligations.
Agents respect these as protected time.)_

## Hobbies + restoration

{{HOBBIES_RESTORATION}}

_(What {{OWNER_NAME}} does to restore. The agency should protect
this time as fiercely as it protects family time. Burnout is the
slowest goal-killer.)_

## Living context

{{LIVING_CONTEXT}}

_(Home, location, travel patterns, things tied to physical place
that affect scheduling and availability.)_

## Personal projects

{{PERSONAL_PROJECTS}}

_(Things {{OWNER_NAME}} is working on that are not the agency's
work but matter to them. The agency doesn't manage these but
should know they exist when triaging time.)_

## What stays out of work

{{WORK_LIFE_BOUNDARIES}}

_(Explicit boundaries. "Don't schedule work after 7pm." "No work
on Sundays." "Saturday mornings are for the kids." These are hard
rules, not preferences.)_

